üìò Public Key Infrastructure ‚Äì Session 10
PKCS, FIPS 140-2 & XCA CA Lab
(PG-DITISS August 2025)

üü¢ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. PKCS stands for:
A. Public Key Cryptography System
B. Public Key Cryptography Standards
C. Private Key Cryptography Standard
D. Protected Key Crypto Suite

2. PKCS standards are developed by:
A. ISO
B. NIST
C. RSA Laboratories
D. IEEE

3. PKCS standards are related to:
A. Symmetric encryption
B. Asymmetric cryptography
C. Network routing
D. File systems

4. FIPS stands for:
A. Federal Internet Processing Standard
B. Federal Information Processing Standard
C. Fast Information Processing System
D. Flexible Internet Protection Standard

5. FIPS 140-2 specifies standards for:
A. Hash algorithms
B. Cryptographic modules
C. Network protocols
D. Certificates only

6. Which organization publishes FIPS standards?
A. ISO
B. IEEE
C. NIST
D. RSA

7. XCA is mainly used for:
A. Encryption only
B. Certificate & key management
C. Network monitoring
D. Intrusion detection

8. A CA certificate is used to:
A. Encrypt files
B. Sign other certificates
C. Compress data
D. Generate hashes

9. Browser warnings occur mainly due to:
A. Weak encryption
B. Self-signed certificates
C. Expired password
D. Firewall rules

10. Importing a CA certificate into browser helps to:
A. Encrypt traffic
B. Remove trust warnings
C. Increase speed
D. Compress data

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE MCQs (10)
11. Which PKCS standard defines RSA cryptography?
A. PKCS#5
B. PKCS#7
C. PKCS#1
D. PKCS#12

12. PKCS#12 is used for:
A. Key exchange
B. Storing private key + certificate
C. Hashing
D. Digital signature only

