A. 2
B. 3
C. 4
D. 5

16. Higher FIPS level means:
A. Faster encryption
B. Stronger physical & logical security
C. Larger key size only
D. Better compression

17. In XCA, the first step to issue certificates is to:
A. Create CSR
B. Create CA
C. Create website
D. Import browser

18. Website certificates are usually issued to:
A. IP address
B. MAC address
C. Domain name
D. Port number

19. Which certificate type is used for HTTPS?
A. Client certificate
B. Code signing certificate
C. Server certificate
D. Root certificate

20. Importing CA certificate into browser establishes:
A. Encryption
B. Trust
C. Authentication
D. Hashing

üî∫ ADVANCED MCQs (10)
