B. No trusted CA signature
C. Short key length
D. Expired validity

24. CA hierarchy improves PKI by:
A. Eliminating root CA
B. Distributing trust & risk
C. Faster encryption
D. Removing certificates

25. In XCA, issuing a website certificate requires:
A. Public key only
B. CSR from website
C. Private key of CA only
D. Hash only

26. Importing CA certificate into browser does which action?
A. Encrypts browser data
B. Adds CA to trust store
C. Revokes certificates
D. Generates keys

27. HTTPS trust is established when:
A. Certificate is self-signed
B. Browser trusts issuing CA
C. Key size is large
D. Hash is SHA-1

28. Which PKCS standard is commonly used in email security (S/MIME)?
A. PKCS#1
B. PKCS#7
C. PKCS#8
D. PKCS#11

29. FIPS 140-2 focuses mainly on:
A. Algorithms only
B. Key management only
C. Cryptographic module security
D. Certificate formats

30. CCEE TRAP in Session 10 usually tests:
A. PKCS number vs purpose
B. FIPS 140-2 meaning
C. CA vs self-signed logic
D. All of the above

